Hopefully I can work with [[Ragel]] more now that I'm working with [[Ruby]] more!

Here's an example I hacked up with the help of the [http://www.devchix.com/2008/01/13/a-hello-world-for-ruby-on-ragel-60/ dev chix]:

<pre class="sh_ruby">
%%{
    machine multistep;

    default = ^0;

    anchorfin := |*

        'z' @ {
            puts "zoro";
            fgoto main;
        }
        default;

    *|;

    main := (

        'o' @ { $barf = ""; }
        |'h' @ { $barf << "hello world!" }
        |'w' @ { $barf << "welcome" }
        |'z' @ { fgoto anchorfin; }
        |'q' @ { puts $barf }

   )*;

}%%

  data = 'owhwzzwwhwq'
  %% write data;
  %% write init;
  %% write exec;
</pre>

Not too fancy, but hey.

